Defendant waives their right to appear in person and Court accepts waiver. State calls Deputy Brandon Ring to testify- is sworn and testifies. 
Cross examination by the Defense. Witness is released. State asks for bind over. 
Court binds matter over for ARGN in Branch 1.

(3:16 PM case called.) All parties and court personnel appear via Zoom. 
Defendant Jordan M Roberts does not appear in court or via Zoom. Attorney Zebulon Patek in court for Jordan M Roberts. Prosecuting attorney Andrew Gunderson in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Attorney Patek advises the defendant is in custody in Pierce County.
Court was not aware the defendant was in custody in another county.
Parties request clerk to make contact with Pierce County and have the defendant appear.
Parties will recall the case shortly.
(3:31 PM case recalled.) All parties and court personnel appear via Zoom. 
Defendant Jordan M Roberts does not appear in court or via Zoom. Attorney Zebulon Patek in court for Jordan M Roberts. Prosecuting attorney Andrew Gunderson in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Attorney Patek advises Pierce County wasn't aware the defendant had court in Eau Claire County today.
Parties request to schedule new date.
State requests the Court find good cause to extend the time limits. Court orders finds good cause to extend time limits for preliminary hearing.
Preliminary Hearing scheduled for October 18, 2022 at 2 pm.
